r it while I was playing EQ as well.  Not going out with friends, letting life slowly drift away until it feels almost impossible to go back to it.  I'd played other online games before EQ, and although UO did a good job of this as well, it wasn't quite as bad.  <br><br>Anyway.. food for thought.  <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaraxasxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>araxas xev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:25:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> Touchy subject :P<br><br>I quit too a few months ago, but even when playing it was strictly a hobby, and I never let it interfere with real life commitments, relationships, and work (well hehe guess there were a few times I was up too late playing). I know and met a very large number of people in a boat similar to mine, casual players who played EQ within reason just like anyone would persue any hobby.<br><br>But for every person like this I met, I'd also meet one for whom EverQuest was not just a game, but a serious &quot;escape&quot; or even replacement for real life. Among this group I think you're probably right that there are a good number of them who might be considered clinically depressed.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=makabrei>Makabrei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:30:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> Actually, i find my self getting depressed when i cut my self off from games. Not just EQ. Games are what i do. Its the thing i feel confident at. I know im good at them and it makes me happy to play and compete and win in games. Each person is different though, and i do other things besides game so i'd imagine people that cut off social lifes to play EQ would get depressed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalliasylurian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kallia Sylurian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:58:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/lig/g/r/greenvix/bookfaerymini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> I think there can be a point in someone's life that something can replace what is really considered a &quot;life&quot; to many.  Once upon a time I was a true EQ addict and there were situations where I felt I needed to escape.  But now I have learned there is more to life than EQ.  I still play on a regular basis, but I don't let it interfere with things that I believe are important in life.  <br><br>I can't say that many people who play a lot of EQ are clinically depressed, this just might be the way that they enjoy their free time.  It might just be that EQ is a place where they are happiest.  I love the friends I have met while playing Everquest.  They are true friends and they give support when it is needed.  I also love my friends and family in real life and they have come to understand that sometimes I just need to &quot;get away&quot;.  <br><br>EQ doesn't control my life the way it did a year ago, but I still enjoy playing.  It's all a matter of perspective and priorities.  If this makes you happy, play.  If you play and you feel anger than maybe there are things you need to look at in your life to help you.  I'm no psychologist, but I do know the addiction that can get to you...<br><br>Playing games is just one of those things that some people enjoy more than others.  If you like playing EQ, keep playing it to the fullest, but don't let it overrun your life and take away other things that you can enjoy... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quiksilverroxdasox>Quiksilver Roxdasox</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 12:14:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> i wouldnt say that the question is &quot;how many EQ players are depressed&quot; but how many people in the united states are depressed. that'd be a pretty large number for people that are just &quot;depressed,&quot; nothing clinical. its kinda what modern society does =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucokoanuttmunkey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cokoanutt Munkey</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://binksy.50megs.com/headpic2.jpg WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 12:28:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://binksy.50megs.com/headpic2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> the world sucks.  eq is an escape, that doesn't suck quite as much.  That is all. <p>People call me Binky...and you can too!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelthana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelthana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 12:31:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> This is kinda like saying, &quot;heavy metal lyrics incite murder&quot;. No, murderers just prefer heavy metal. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And I think depressed people looking for an escape from what they see as an unsatisfying life often turn to fantasy in the form of online games. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udrakinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 12:39:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> I have a really bad case of depression (well, its actually more that i have really big highs and really bad lows, even though i'm low more than naught)<br><br>I don't think it has much to do with eq though, or even computer games, i've tried quitting but it doesnt help or hurt.<br><br>Of course, I'm not depressed because of eq, and i dont have a love / hate relationship with it either (Playing eq makes me depressed b/c i'm playing a game and it is pathetic, but oh now i'm sad i wanna play my rogue)<br><br><br>I think you should look more to the fact of the high rate of depression in our society in genral. After you look at that, its no wonder people flock to eq and other online games.<br><br>They:<br>1) Don't require a deep coversation or real interaction with people. It's hard holding a coversation when your really depressed, that isnt whining<br><br>2) It keeps you busy. While watching TV or driving my mind wanders to things that depress me, but in eq you can focus on pulling or whatever and it doesnt give you a chance to worry.<br><br>3) You get a sense of friendship, and people rely on you. feeling bad-ass about your character is good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udawisemonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaWiseMonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 7:52:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> Me depressed no........... Daring Yes.......... Meaning on EQ you can do things that you would not get a chance to do in RL more than Once......... EQ as I see it is a chance to do things taht you would not get to try in RL more than once......... What I mean by that is say You wanna see how good your safefall is you climb up to the top of the Wizzy Spire and take a Leap and................you die =\......... Well Guess what You can run back and get your body and do soemthing else..... Now there would be no 2nd chance if you tried that in RL hehe........ EQ to me is about challenging yourself to do something you don't think you can and if you fail you can try again until you get it right........ Ppl I think are more inclined to do this on EQ becuase the Real world is not as forgiving.......... EQ does not take over the RL when I have something to do I get it done......... It doesn't come in between me and Mine there is no game in the world that can do that hehe.......... It is fun to Meet new ppl and get with old friends and do stuff that when you were LvL 6 you thought impossible though............<br><br>&quot;Brother&quot; Ychang Kang <p>A man had a friend, a friend had a plan, the plan was a dream, the dream was..........Darksphere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugabus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gabus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 8:02:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> &quot;I wake up in the morning for classes, and hit work after 2 a day, and I'm full of energy instead of feeling tired. &quot;<br><br><br>Some of that is simply from going back to the Gym...at first, it tires you out, but after the initial training of your body to adapt to it, it actually increases your energy level overall...<br><br><br>I am sort of a &quot;binge&quot; EQ player...I play alot, too much in fact, untill my RL is affected adversly, like i dont complete work, I skip the Gym a couple times, I skip an outing with RL friends ECT...Then I will swing 360, admonish myself for being weak, and refocus on what is MY priorities, Family, RL friends, work ECT... once it is back on track (usually a couple weeks) I will go back to EQ, little bits at a time, untill the cycle starts again...<br><br>A little Neurotic....you betcha... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br> <p>Gabus Copperdrachon<BR>51st season Paladin <BR>Niccollo <BR>11 th season Warrior <BR>Immortal Power<BR>Rodcet Nife <BR><BR>"Damn...LOH'd the mob again!" <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uamaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaara</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 8:11:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.stny.rr.com/ehl/ABLuclin.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> Yeah, Quiksilver, in pre-modern times man lived in a state of idyllic Nature, al