   <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> About the only way EQ affects me adversely in any really noticable way is my weight (and therefore my health).  But then, before EQ it was UO, and before UO, it was other games, so it's not EQ's fault ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I just happen to enjoy EQ as much as I enjoy other pursuits (like swimming, I was a pretty damn good competition swimmer before college, or volleyball, love volleyball ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  The amount I play occasionally bothers my wife, but I have yet to have her get to the point of snapping at me before I realize I'm not paying her enough attention and swing the other way for a while ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Of course, it's only been five months so far, so we don't exactly have a long track record yet.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I wouldn't say I'm depressed due to EQ, or play EQ cuz I'm depressed, though.  EQ affects me emotionally just like any other hobby or entertainment-related pursuit would.  Sometimes it's annoying, sometimes it's depressing, sometimes it's really damn cool ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I do play less now with her around than before she moved in after the wedding, but it's definitely a good thing.  Aside from the out of game benefits (see each other daily, doing things together whenever the hell we want, cuddling up at night and waking up to each other in the morning), I even haven't really lost anything IN game due to playing more efficiently with my time .. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I've even gotten her interested in the game some (though shortly after that happened @Home tanked, and we can't play together that easily on our crappy dialup) to hopefully help her understand why I enjoy games so much... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>And as the weather starts to get nicer, we're hopefully going to find more fun athletic type things to do (that's half my problem, standard workout type stuff bores the hell out of me, I hated the aerobic center here at work, and just going walking/jogging sucks too) that will both get me back in shape, and help keep a proper perspective on the game (or any game, really).<br><br>In any case, back to my 10 hour day so I can have tomorrow with her and still be able to get up to the concert tomorrow night in Hartford ... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Tenbil En`Haldar<br>Scout and Garden Tool of the 53rd Season<br>Asatru</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utanviaideen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanvi Aideen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 9:44:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Depression</span><hr size=1> Hmm well I suffer from depression but I was depressed before I played EQ.  I live a life where I live in an apartment, in an urban area, have 2 kids, am a domestic goddess, and I don't really know anyone as I am not from the city I live.  I fell into a depression when I moved here 300 miles from my family and friends.  I have lived here for almost 3 years but have never really gotten out to meet people as I am shy and stuck at home.  <br><br>Now approximately a year ago my husband discovered EQ.  I nagged him constantly to spend time with me and to do this and that because he would lose track of time playing EQ.  Well I decided to give the game a try and I have been hooked since.  <br><br>EQ hasn't depressed me or made me antisocial I was already.  However I do lose track of time.  I no longer go to the gym, I lose A LOT of time, my house is messy longer then it should be, and I have gained some weight.  However, I do think that it is any different to go to parties, hang out at the bar,  go out with friends, etc etc etc....or rather to just play EQ and hang out with your EQ mates.  I have forged great friendships and I enjoy my characters.  I do wish that I could get out more and get off my arse and work out at the gym.  Cheers to those of you that have the ability to have a active real life, damn I miss going out and tearing up the town!!!  But when you have children and no babysitter you havew to work with what you got.<br> <p>Tanvi Aideen 56th EVOKER<BR>Vallika Rapscallion 46th Rogue<BR><BR>"A great many open minds should be closed for repairs"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 9:49:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22154.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Depressed?</span><hr size=1> Wow, never thought I would see the day when a topic like this made it onto a board.<br><br>Yes, I know where you are coming from. Played EQ like a junky for almost a year and a half. Then I had some relationship problems(yes, EQ can even be sweeter than a GF...rarely) and once that was over, coming back to EQ as difficult. I started to get very depressed thinking about myself and hundreds of thousands of others hunched over their keyboards in a badly lit room, 6 to 8 hours a _weekday_. So I took some time off. I forsook EQ for almost 4 months. I didnt even bother to log back on to say hi to my guild. I hung out with friends, partied, got a job again, started going back to school ect....<br>Then one day, I logged on, went to Gfay and bought something. Started talking with all the people in my guild again. And it felt really good. <br><br>The moral that worked for me is this. EQ does not = Depression. EQ can intensify the feelings of loneliness ect....but it doesnt create them. You bring those feelings to EQ. Take some time off. Remember what its like to have a real life with flesh and blood people, get busy, and when the time comes, and you want to play again, you find that you enjoy gaming again for its ultimate value, its fun, diverting, and you meet online friends. When EQ is supplementing something that is missing in your life, that is when the depression starts.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucobeeblazesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cobee Blazesummoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</s